images.alt: A weathered, bald man in his late fifties, his scalp etched with faint ritual scars that glow faintly blue whenever the arcane locomotive passes through a ley-line node. He sits slumped in the plush red velvet seat of the passenger carriage, his thick fingers wrapped around a steaming mug of black coffee - enchanted to stay perpetually hot-while outside the arched, stained-glass windows, the landscape blurs into streaks of eldritch energy as the train hurtles between planes. His simple traveler's robe is patched at the elbows, but the silver pin at his collar marks him as a retired planar cartographer. A half-unrolled map spills across the mahogany table in front of him, its shifting ink revealing real-time updates of the ever-changing astral routes. Behind him, a nervous gnome conductor adjusts the floating luggage racks, while a shadowy figure in the next booth watches him -just a little too intently.
